<H3> <TI>   Judiciary Police Director Says Drug Trafficking Has </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Judiciary Police Director Says Drug Trafficking Has </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
`Stabilized' 

<F P=102>   LD1404105294 Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network in Portuguese 
0900 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1404105294 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Mario Mendes, director of the Judiciary Police, 
told us this morning that drugs trafficking has stabilized in 
Portugal: 
  [Begin recording] Mendes: According to 
data we have available, we can notice that trafficking for 
consumption in Portugal has stabilized, but we have to be alert 
to any possibility of an increase. 
  Unidentified correspondent: And what about 
Portugal being used as a route for trafficking into Europe? 
  Mendes: It is still a main route for hashish and 
cocaine. We can see this through the amounts we have been 
seizing. Portugal continues to have a main role for the entry 
of hashish and cocaine. [end recording] [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

