<F P=100> WEST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Visit U.S. for Talks on Fighting Drugs, Crime </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials Visit U.S. for Talks on Fighting Drugs, Crime </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1804103494 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1015 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1804103494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Istanbul, April 17 (A.A.) -- Istanbul Security Chief 
Mehmet Agar and Unal Erkan, state of emergency region governor, 
left for the United States on Monday. 
  Agar told reporters at Istanbul's Ataturk Airport before his 
departure that during his visit they will meet with Federal 
Bureau of Investigation (FBI) officials and Drug Enforcement 
Administration (DEA) officials. 
  During the meetings, possibilities for new methods of 
fighting drugs and organized crime will be discussed. 
  Agar said it will be a very useful visit in terms of 
strengthening present positive relations. 
  Both officials will return to Turkey this weekend. 

</TEXT>

