<H3> <TI>   Over Three Hundred Forty Kg of Narcotic `Raw Materials' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Over Three Hundred Forty Kg of Narcotic `Raw Materials' </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Seized   During March 

<F P=102> AU1204140094 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 8 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU1204140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: ``For Whom Is the Border a </F>
Nuisance?''] 
  [Text] As reported by the Press Service of Ukraine's State 
Committee for Issues of Protection of Ukraine's State Border, 
the number of attempts to cross our borders illegally is 
increasing. Last month, border guards detained 1,112 
trespassers, among whom citizens of Afghanistan, Turkey (Kurds), 
Vietnam, Syria, and some Balkan countries constituted 78 percent. 
  The authorities confiscated from the border violators, in 
particular, smugglers, 2.5 tonnes of technological mercury, more 
than three tonnes of nonferrous metals, over 30 units of various 
types of weapons, 340.3 kilograms of narcotic raw materials, and 
so on. 
  The State Committee for Borders points out that, with the 
strengthening of border and customs control, the activity of 
those criminal groups that struggle for influence on the 
railroad transport system and that accompany the contraband 
goods by road has intensified. 

</TEXT>

