<H3> <TI>   Poll Reveals Extent, Types of Drug Use </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Reveals Extent, Types of Drug Use </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94WD0297B Manaus A CRITICA in Portuguese 13 Mar 94 p A3 </F>
<F P=103> 94WD0297B </F>
<F P=104>  Manaus A CRITICA </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Marcia Valeria: "Drug Addiction Begins in </F>
Adolescence"] 
  [Text] A nationwide survey conducted by the Brasmarket 
Institute regarding drug use in Brazil has revealed that 31 
percent of Brazilian drug addicts tried drugs for the first time 
when they were 15 or 16 years old and that 61.4 percent became 
addicted through marijuana. Cocaine ranks second in Brazilian 
preferences at 40.9 percent. The researchers interviewed 800 
individuals in different capitals and claim that these data 
reflect reality in Manaus. 
  The survey also reveals that 58.4 percent of those 
interviewed became acquainted with drugs through friends, and 
61.7 percent deny being dependent or addicted. Of the 800 people 
interviewed, all had tried some kind of drug once in their life, 
29.4 percent of them only for fun. 
  Another finding by the survey is that 94.1 percent of those 
interviewed have drug users in their circle of friends. 


