<F P=106> [Article: "More Ganja Found on the Beach"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Less than one week after 850 pounds of ganja was 
found washed up on a Cayman Brac beach, a further 110 pounds of 
the drug was discovered on the beach at Old Man Bay in North 
Side early Wednesday morning (9 February). 
  The initial police report said the ganja appeared to have 
been in the water for some time. Drugs Squad officers were to 
examine the ganja Wednesday and Thursday to determine if the 
drugs were originally destined for Cayman or part of a shipment 
dumped at sea and washed ashore by accident. 
  The 110 pounds of ganja would have a street value of 
slightly 
more than CI$105,000. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

