<F P=106> [Report by Oscar Galvis from the "AM-PM" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Upon arriving in the United States from London, 
Prosecutor General Gustavo de Greiff said President Cesar 
Gaviria's administration is subservient to the United States. 
De Greiff called several U.S. officials liars and accused 
President Gaviria of unnecessarily criticizing him for his fight 
against drug traffickers. De Greiff said the president wanted 
to calm the U.S. Government's temper by attacking him. The 
prosecutor general said of the Colombian Government: They 
wanted to make themselves seem subservient to the U.S. 
Government by attacking me. 
  As for the accusations that Colombia is a narcodemocracy, de 
Greiff said it is an exaggerated perception and once again 
called Senator Kerry and Assistant Attorney General Harris liars. 

