<H3> <TI>   Number of Foreigners Involved in Drug Arrests, Seizures in </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Number of Foreigners Involved in Drug Arrests, Seizures in </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
1993   Reported 

<F P=102> 94WD0317A Kingston THE DAILY GLEANER in English 20 Feb 94 p 
24 </F>

<F P=103> 94WD0317A </F>
<F P=104>  Kingston THE DAILY GLEANER </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Article: "Canadian on Drug Rap"] </F>
  [Text] Police have arrested and charged the second Canadian 
in eight days for breaches of the Dangerous Drug Act. 
  Arrested and charged is Clivette Wood, 33, of Ontario, 
Canada. She is scheduled to appear before the Montego Bay RM 
Court tomorrow. 
  According to the police report, Wood was in the process of 
boarding an outgoing flight to Canada, from the Donald Sangster 
International Airport on Friday, when she was searched and .45 
kilograms of ganja found strapped to her body. 
  Last weekend another Canadian, 41-year-old Jean Lamount, of 
Quebec, was held at the Donald Sangster International Airport 
and a quantity of hash oil found in his possession. 
  Last year 1,096 foreigners were arrested and charged under 
the Dangerous Drug Act; 1,030 were held for attempting to export 
ganja, 52 were held for cocaine and 14 for smoking ganja, 144 of 
the offenders were from Canada. 
  Meanwhile, the police are also reporting that 22.7 kilograms 
of ganja was found in an empty container at the Montego Bay 
Freeport yesterday morning. 
  Security personnel carrying out routine check found the drug 
concealed in the container, which was about to be loaded on a 
cargo ship destined for Chicago, United States. No arrest was 
made. 

</TEXT>

