<H3> <TI>   Record Seizure of Pills In Jalisco Prison </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Record Seizure of Pills In Jalisco Prison </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94WB0033E Mexico City EXCELSIOR in Spanish 31 Mar 94 STATES 
Section pp 1, 4 </F>

<F P=103> 94WB0033E </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City EXCELSIOR </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Eduardo Chimely Chimely] </F>
  [Text] Guadalajara, Jalisco, 30 March--Some 12,493 
psychotropic pills (the largest number in the local jail's 
history) were confiscated by guards at the state crime 
prevention prison. This announcement was made today by its head, 
Maricela Gomez Cobos. 
  According to the information furnished, the inmates Jaime 
Bugarain Barajas, Juan Gallegos Hernandez, Ricardo Gonzalez 
Almaraz, Felipe de Jesus Esparza Lopez, and Oscar Ortiz 
Gonzalez, confined in cell 77 of that jail's third dormitory, 
had concealed a box containing 12,493 pills of the Roche brand, 
each of two milligrams. They were being sold inside the prison 
for between 5,000 and 10,000 new pesos. 
  The drugs were placed at the disposal of the Federal Public 
Prosecutor's Office, and a new trial will be opened against the 
culpable inmates. All of them have been remanded for theft, 
assault, and crimes against health, according to the 
aforementioned prison authority, who described this as the 
largest confiscation in the institution's history. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

