<F P=100> WEST EUROPE </F>
<F P=101> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Seizure From German Couple Called `Biggest Blow' Against </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seizure From German Couple Called `Biggest Blow' Against </PHRASE></F></HT>


<TEXT>
Heroin   Cartels 

<F P=102> NC2204103794 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 0900 GMT 22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2204103794 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>
BFN 

  [Text] Customs officers at the Kipoi checkpoint in the 
area of Evros [on the Turkish border] early this morning succeed 
in striking the biggest blow in recent years against the 
international heroin cartels. Customs officers discovered 121 
kilos of heroin hidden in a camper. The camper belongs to 
German nationals (Juergen Maert), 31, and his wife (Dona 
Annette), 26, who had left Turkey heading for London. During 
the interrogation, the Germans told the customs officers that 
they knew of the heroin's existence in their camper, and that 
they were going to receive 100,000 German marks upon its 
delivery in London. The drugs and camper were confiscated and 
the two Germans will appear before the Alexandroupolis 
prosecutor within the day. 

</TEXT>

