<F P=101> INDIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade in Ozone Depleting Substances Banned </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trade in Ozone Depleting Substances Banned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94WN0217A Madras THE HINDU in English 9 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 94WN0217A </F>
<F P=104>  Madras THE HINDU </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

  [Text] New Delhi, Feb 8--Being a party to the Montreal 
Protocol, to check emission of substances which deplete the 
ozone layer, the Union Government has prohibited import and 
export of eight substances with countries which are not parties 
to the protocol. 
  The eight substances are trichloro flouro methane, dichloro 
difluoro methane, trichloro triflouro methane, dichloro 
tetrafluoro ethane, chloro pentafluoro ethane, bromo chloro 
diflouro methane, bromo triflouro methane and dibromo tetrafuoro 
ethane. Trade in these commodities with countries which are 
parties to the Montreal protocol is permitted without a licence. 

</TEXT>

