  [Text] Oleg Padenko: The fact that yet another 
nuclear submarine is being dismantled at the Zvezda Works was 
immediately known in the Maritime Kray. After all, the question 
immediately arose as to what to do with the water from the 
submarine, polluted with radiation, since the notorious TNT-5 
tanker, like others, is full to overflowing with 
life-threatening waste. This is in the center of the Bolshoy 
Kamen town, quite near to Vladivostok. [video shows port 
facilities, vessels, residential buildings nearby] 
  Nor is there any protection against the impending disaster. 
Local projects to treat the waste are unrealistic and the 
Japanese assistance is hanging in the air. 
  It is precisely for this reason that the interdepartmental 
commission working at the Zvezda Works made a sensational 
decision on the necessity to discharge the liquid radioactive 
waste into the Sea of Japan, as was done before, because nothing 
else can be done. 
  Ahead is the dismantling of a further number of nuclear 
submarines, more than 40. 

